    "causal_summary": "There is no convergence-gated loop that assembles implementation-ready context from the existing codebase. `/speckit:plan` discovers context ad-hoc and `/speckit:implement` relies on whatever the plan captured, so reusable code is missed, stale references and context-rot creep in, and there is no saturation signal for \"enough context gathered.\" A first build closed that gap, but it landed as a host-driven loop that does not yet use the shared runtime's durability and validation layer as fully as the mature deep loops do.",
